                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Large marble slab, broken in multiple fragments and restored. Height 76 cm; width 112.7 cm; depth 3 cm. The front carries a relief carved with a geometric design which resembles a shield. At a later date a set of five holes has been drilled through the upper part of the slab, parallel to the top edge.</p>
